  "body": "The usage of isMounted before React.renderComponent results on an invalid access. Of all methods, this one is often used outside of the component to guard access to other methods. Is it really an anti-pattern like described in https://gist.github.com/sebmarkbage/8928067 ? I understand when it comes to other methods, but not in the isMounted case.\n",
